			    STPJS 325</div>
  <p class="std">The disappointment of hopes and expectations at the resurrection would be indescribably
  dreadful.<span class="footRef">1</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Angels and Spirits</div>
  <p class="std">The organization of the spiritual and heavenly worlds,<span class="footRef">2</span> and of spiritual and heavenly beings,
  was agreeable to the most perfect order and harmony:<span class="footRef">3</span> their limits and bounds were fixed<span class="footRef">4</span>
  irrevocably, and voluntarily subscribed to in their heavenly estate by themselves, and were by our
  first parents<span class="footRef">5</span> subscribed to upon the earth. Hence the importance of embracing and subscribing to
  principles of eternal truth by all men upon the earth that expect eternal life.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <p class="std">I assure the Saints that truth, in reference to these matters, can and may be known through the
  revelations of God in the way of His ordinances,<span class="footRef">7</span> and in answer to prayer.<span class="footRef">8</span> The Hebrew Church
  &ldquo;came unto the spirits of just men made perfect,<span class="footRef">9</span> and unto an innumerable company of angels,<span class="footRef">10</span> unto
  God the Father of all,<span class="footRef">11</span> and to Jesus Christ the Mediator of the new covenant.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">12</span> What did they learn
  by coming to the spirits of just men made perfect?<span class="footRef">13</span> Is it written? No. What they learned has not
  been and could not have been written.<span class="footRef">14</span> What object was gained by this communication with the
  spirits of the just?<span class="footRef">15</span> It was the established order of the kingdom<span class="footRef">16</span> of God: The keys of power and
  knowledge<span class="footRef">17</span> were with them to communicate to the Saints. Hence the importance of understanding
  the distinction between the spirits of the just and angels.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <p class="std">Spirits can only be revealed in flaming fire and glory.<span class="footRef">19</span> Angels have advanced further, their
  light and glory being tabernacled;<span class="footRef">20</span> and hence they appear in bodily shape.<span class="footRef">21</span> The spirits of just men<span class="footRef">22</span>
  are made ministering servants to those who<span class="footRef">23</span> are sealed unto life eternal,<span class="footRef">24</span> and it is through them that
  the sealing power comes down.</p>
  <p class="std">Patriarch Adams is now one of the spirits of the just men made perfect;<span class="footRef">25</span> and, if revealed now,
  must be revealed in fire;<span class="footRef">26</span> and the glory could not be endured.<span class="footRef">27</span> Jesus showed Himself to His
  disciples, and they thought it was His spirit, and they were afraid to approach His spirit.<span class="footRef">28</span> Angels
  have advanced higher in knowledge and power than spirits.</p>
  <p class="std">Concerning Brother James Adams, it should appear strange that so good and so great a man was
  hated. The deceased ought never to have had an enemy. But so it was. Wherever</p>
